problems.description:
Mock an email service using Mockito to test business logic in isolation.

```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class UserRegistrationServiceTest {
    @Mock EmailService emailService; // mock — no real emails sent
    @Mock UserRepository userRepo;
    @InjectMocks UserRegistrationService service; // real service, mocked dependencies

    @Test void register_newUser_sendsWelcomeEmail() {
        // Arrange:
        when(userRepo.existsByEmail("alice@test.com")).thenReturn(false);
        when(userRepo.save(any(User.class))).thenAnswer(i -> i.getArgument(0));
        // Act:
        service.register("Alice", "alice@test.com");
        // Assert:
        verify(emailService).sendWelcome("alice@test.com", "Alice"); // was it called?
        verify(emailService, never()).sendWelcome(contains("error"), anyString()); // not called with error
    }

    @Test void register_duplicateEmail_throwsAndNoEmail() {
        when(userRepo.existsByEmail("alice@test.com")).thenReturn(true);
        assertThrows(DuplicateEmailException.class, () -> service.register("Alice", "alice@test.com"));
        verifyNoInteractions(emailService); // email NOT sent on failure
    }
}
```

**Key insight:** Mocks replace real dependencies to test ONE class in isolation. `when().thenReturn()` stubs; `verify()` checks interactions. Never mock the class under test.

